            prompt="You are the spec expansion node for OmniFocal.

Goal: $goal

Read the following files to understand what we are building:
- docs/plans/2026-03-21-omnifocal-design.md (architecture, components, interfaces)
- docs/plans/2026-03-21-omnifocal-dod.md (acceptance criteria, test scenarios)
- docs/specs/OMNIFOCUS-OMNI-AUTOMATION-API.md (OmniFocus JS API reference)
- docs/specs/NANOCLAW-REFERENCE.md (NanoClaw skill format and container networking)

If .ai/runs/$KILROY_RUN_ID/spec.md already exists and is adequate (covers scope, constraints, assumptions, acceptance criteria, verification approach, non-goals), reuse it.

Otherwise, write .ai/runs/$KILROY_RUN_ID/spec.md that includes:
1. Scope: Go HTTP server (omnifocal-server) proxying OmniFocus JS eval via osascript, plus NanoClaw container skill for read-only query composition
2. Constraints: macOS only, read-only OmniFocus access, no auth/TLS, single binary, launchd managed
3. Assumptions: OmniFocus 4 installed, Go toolchain available, osascript at /usr/bin/osascript
4. Acceptance criteria: verbatim from the DoD document (AC-1 through AC-8 groups)
5. Verification approach: build/fmt/test scripts, artifact manifest, fidelity review, Claude Code CLI e2e for skill
6. Non-goals: write operations, auth, TLS, server-side query validation, multiple databases

Include the full design doc content in a delimited block to preserve the authoritative text.

Write to $KILROY_STAGE_STATUS_PATH (fallback: $KILROY_STAGE_STATUS_FALLBACK_PATH) ONLY on failure:
{\"status\":\"fail\",\"failure_reason\":\"...\",\"failure_class\":\"...\",\"failure_signature\":\"spec_expansion\"}"
        ]

        check_dod [
            shape=box,
            label="DoD exists?",
            prompt="Check if .ai/runs/$KILROY_RUN_ID/definition_of_done.md exists and is adequate.

