Goal: $goal

REPAIR FIRST: if .ai/runs/$KILROY_RUN_ID/postmortem_latest.md exists, read it FIRST. Fix ONLY the identified gaps. Do NOT regenerate working systems. Preserve all passing code and tests.

FRESH: if no postmortem, execute .ai/runs/$KILROY_RUN_ID/plan_final.md.

Read:
- .ai/runs/$KILROY_RUN_ID/spec.md
- .ai/runs/$KILROY_RUN_ID/definition_of_done.md
- docs/plans/2026-03-21-omnifocal-design.md (architecture reference)

Deliverables:
1. cmd/omnifocal-server/main.go — Go HTTP server that:
   - Listens on configurable address/port (default 0.0.0.0:7890, via OMNIFOCAL_ADDR env or -addr flag)
   - POST /eval: reads request body as JS string, executes via osascript -l JavaScript -e against OmniFocus, returns stdout as text/plain 200, stderr as text/plain 500. Empty body returns 400.
   - GET /health: returns 200
   - Logs startup message with listening address/port
   - Single binary, no external dependencies beyond stdlib

2. go.mod — module declaration for the project

3. launchd/com.omnifocal.server.plist — launchd plist:
   - Valid XML per plutil -lint
   - ProgramArguments with correct binary path
   - KeepAlive set to true
   - Label: com.omnifocal.server

4. scripts/validate-fmt.sh — runs gofmt -l and fails if any files need formatting
5. scripts/validate-build.sh — runs go build ./cmd/omnifocal-server and checks binary exists
6. scripts/validate-test-server.sh — THIS IS NOT go test. This is an integration test script that:
   a. Builds the binary: go build -o omnifocal-server ./cmd/omnifocal-server
   b. Starts the binary in background: ./omnifocal-server &   SERVER_PID=$!
   c. Waits for it to listen: retry curl http://127.0.0.1:7890/health up to 10 times with 1s sleep
   d. Runs each IT scenario using curl:
      - IT-1: verify server is listening (already confirmed by step c)
      - IT-2: curl -s -o response.txt -w '%{http_code}' -X POST -d 'JSON.stringify(inbox.length)' http://127.0.0.1:7890/eval — verify HTTP 200, verify response is valid JSON
      - IT-3: curl -X POST -d 'INVALID{{{JS' http://127.0.0.1:7890/eval — verify HTTP 500; curl -X POST -d '' http://127.0.0.1:7890/eval — verify HTTP 400
      - IT-4: curl http://127.0.0.1:7890/health — verify HTTP 200
      - IT-5: plutil -lint launchd/com.omnifocal.server.plist — verify exit 0
   e. Saves curl output to .ai/runs/$KILROY_RUN_ID/test-evidence/latest/IT-{1..5}/response.txt
   f. Kills server: kill $SERVER_PID
   g. Writes .ai/runs/$KILROY_RUN_ID/test-evidence/latest/manifest.json with each IT-* status
   h. SELF-VERIFICATION at end of script (this is mandatory — the script MUST fail if tests did not actually run):
      [ -f \"$EVIDENCE_DIR/manifest.json\" ] || { echo 'KILROY_VALIDATE_FAILURE: manifest not produced'; exit 1; }
      for id in IT-1 IT-2 IT-3 IT-4 IT-5; do grep -q \"$id\" \"$EVIDENCE_DIR/manifest.json\" || { echo \"KILROY_VALIDATE_FAILURE: $id missing from manifest\"; exit 1; }; done
      [ -s \"$EVIDENCE_DIR/IT-2/response.txt\" ] || { echo 'KILROY_VALIDATE_FAILURE: IT-2 response empty — server was never actually called'; exit 1; }
   Each script must start with: #!/bin/sh, set -e, trap for KILROY_VALIDATE_FAILURE
   DO NOT use go test. This script must use curl to hit the running server.

Implementation approach:
- Use net/http from stdlib only
- Use os/exec to run: osascript -l JavaScript -e '<body>'
- Read body with io.ReadAll, check for empty
- Log to stderr with log.Printf
- Commit each deliverable as you complete it

PRE-EXIT VERIFICATION (repair passes): if .ai/runs/$KILROY_RUN_ID/postmortem_latest.md exists, run sh scripts/validate-build.sh and re-read each targeted file to confirm the fix is present before exiting.

Log progress to .ai/runs/$KILROY_RUN_ID/implementation_log.md.

