Verify each acceptance criterion by reading the actual implementation files:

AC-1.1: cmd/omnifocal-server/main.go — verify go build ./cmd/omnifocal-server exits 0 and produces a single executable binary
AC-1.2: cmd/omnifocal-server/main.go — verify the binary starts and listens on configurable address/port (default 0.0.0.0:7890)
AC-2.1: cmd/omnifocal-server/main.go — verify POST /eval with valid OmniFocus JS returns 200 with osascript stdout as text/plain
AC-2.2: cmd/omnifocal-server/main.go — verify POST /eval returns Content-Type text/plain
AC-2.3: cmd/omnifocal-server/main.go — verify POST /eval with invalid JS returns 500 with osascript stderr
AC-2.4: cmd/omnifocal-server/main.go — verify POST /eval with empty body returns 400 Bad Request
AC-3.1: cmd/omnifocal-server/main.go — verify GET /health returns HTTP 200
AC-4.1: launchd/com.omnifocal.server.plist — verify valid XML per plutil -lint
AC-4.2: launchd/com.omnifocal.server.plist — verify ProgramArguments contains correct binary path
AC-4.3: launchd/com.omnifocal.server.plist — verify KeepAlive is set to true

CRITICAL — DO NOT TRUST TOOL NODE RESULTS. You must verify independently:

1. Read .ai/runs/$KILROY_RUN_ID/test-evidence/latest/manifest.json — if it does not exist or is empty, FAIL immediately. The test script was supposed to produce it.
2. For each IT-* in the manifest, read at least one evidence artifact (e.g. IT-2/response.txt) and verify it contains REAL data — not empty, not placeholder, not 'ok'. IT-2 should contain actual OmniFocus task data from a running OmniFocus instance.
3. If manifest exists but evidence files are empty or missing, FAIL. This means the test script claimed success without actually hitting the server.
4. Verify the Go source code actually calls osascript (grep for exec.Command and osascript in main.go).

Write results to .ai/runs/$KILROY_RUN_ID/verify_fidelity_server.md.

Write to $KILROY_STAGE_STATUS_PATH (fallback: $KILROY_STAGE_STATUS_FALLBACK_PATH):
