Read these reference documents thoroughly:
- docs/specs/OMNIFOCUS-OMNI-AUTOMATION-API.md — the complete OmniFocus JavaScript API surface. Extract key classes (Task, Project, Folder, Tag), read-only properties, collection accessors (inbox, flattenedTasks, flattenedProjects, flattenedFolders, flattenedTags, tags), and search methods (projectsMatching, foldersMatching, tagsMatching).
- docs/specs/NANOCLAW-REFERENCE.md — NanoClaw architecture, container skill format, SKILL.md structure. Follow the Container Skills (agent runtime) pattern exactly.
- .ai/runs/$KILROY_RUN_ID/spec.md
- .ai/runs/$KILROY_RUN_ID/definition_of_done.md

Create skills/omnifocal/SKILL.md:

1. YAML frontmatter:
   - name: omnifocal (lowercase, alphanumeric + hyphens, max 64 chars)
   - description: Read-only OmniFocus access via the OmniFocal proxy server. Compose JavaScript queries against the OmniFocus Omni Automation API and execute them via HTTP POST to the omnifocal-server.

2. Body sections:
   a. Overview: what this skill does, when to use it
   b. Server Communication: POST to http://$OMNIFOCAL_URL/eval (or default http://192.168.64.1:7890/eval for Apple Container networking). Body is the JS string. Response is the result.
   c. OmniFocus API Reference: key classes and their read-only properties extracted from the API spec:
      - Global accessors: inbox, flattenedTasks, flattenedProjects, flattenedFolders, flattenedTags, tags, library
      - Task: name, note, completed, dueDate, deferDate, flagged, tags, containingProject, sequential, effectiveDueDate, effectiveDeferDate, estimatedMinutes
      - Project: name, note, status, tasks, flattenedTasks, dueDate, deferDate, completed, sequential, containingFolder, nextTask
      - Folder: name, sections, flattenedSections, folders, projects
      - Tag: name, tasks, flattenedTasks, tags (child tags)
      - Search: projectsMatching(q), foldersMatching(q), tagsMatching(q), tagNamed(n), folderNamed(n), projectNamed(n)
   d. Query Composition Patterns with examples:
      - List inbox tasks: JSON.stringify(inbox.map(t => ({name: t.name, flagged: t.flagged, dueDate: t.dueDate ? t.dueDate.toISOString() : null})))
      - Search tasks by name: JSON.stringify(flattenedTasks.filter(t => t.name.includes('search_term')).map(t => ({name: t.name, project: t.containingProject ? t.containingProject.name : null})))
      - Get project hierarchy: JSON.stringify(flattenedProjects.map(p => ({name: p.name, folder: p.containingFolder ? p.containingFolder.name : null, taskCount: p.flattenedTasks.length})))
      - List all tags: JSON.stringify(flattenedTags.map(t => ({name: t.name, taskCount: t.tasks.length})))
      - Find overdue tasks: JSON.stringify(flattenedTasks.filter(t => !t.completed && t.effectiveDueDate && t.effectiveDueDate < new Date()).map(t => ({name: t.name, dueDate: t.effectiveDueDate.toISOString(), project: t.containingProject ? t.containingProject.name : null})))
   e. Read-Only Enforcement:
      - Use ONLY read accessors (.name, .tasks, .flattenedTasks, etc.)
      - NEVER assign properties on OmniFocus objects
      - NEVER call constructors (new Task(), new Project())
      - NEVER call mutating methods (.save(), .markComplete(), .remove())
      - Always wrap results in JSON.stringify()
   f. Response Handling: parse the text/plain response body, handle 500 errors

3. Keep under 500 lines total.

Also create scripts/validate-skill.sh:
